The paper discusses information security risk assessment methods, which are typically associated with the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The focus on IoT systems suggests a potential fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-categories, as these systems involve large amounts of data and complex software. The mention of cyberspace and the coupling of digital, cyber-physical, and social systems suggests a potential fit with cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories, as these topics relate to the social and ethical implications of technology.
